    "Classification of Human EmotionEmotions can be classified into different categories according to discrete emotion theory or dimensional emotion theory.",
    "Discrete emotion theory assumes that there exists a small number of separate emotions, characterized by coordinated response patterns in physiological, brain, and facial expressions.",
    "The current discrete emotion models mainly include the six emotion models (Fig. 3(b)) proposed by Ekman [18] and the emotion wheel model (Fig.",
    "3(c)) proposed by Plutchik [19].",
    "Among these two discrete models, the most acknowledged one is the basic emotion model."
  ],
